window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A vigilante’s on the loose, dishing out their kind of justice…</b></p> <p>A string of mutilated bodies sees Detective Chief Inspector Whitney Walker back in action. But when she discovers the victims have all been grooming young girls, she fears a vigilante is on the loose. And while she understands the motive, no one is above the law.</p> <p>Once again, she turns to forensic psychologist, Dr Georgina Cavendish, to unravel the cryptic clues. But will they be able to save the next victim from a gruesome death?</p> <p><i>Fatal Justice</i> is the second book in the Cavendish &amp; Walker crime fiction series. If you like your mysteries dark, and with a twist, listen to Sally Rigby’s book today.</p> <p><b>Includes a special bonus note from the author.</b></p>"; 
